1 chapter.
2 (b) Any pretrial risk assessment completed for a person eligible to be released
3 under paragraph (a) of this subsection shall consider the fact that the
4 person cannot provide proof that he or she is a citizen of the United States
5 or otherwise lawfully permitted to be in the United States when determining
6 if the person is a flight risk, is unlikely to appear for trial, or is likely to be a
7 danger to the public if released.
